metadata.name: NFT #182
metadata.description:
This is NFT - Non-Fungible Token released at fxhash.xyz by Shvembldr.

This art is not resolution agnostic and may vary on different devices and screens.

It doesn't make any sense, it's just geometric shapes and moving dots. Sometimes it looks like a liquid splashing to the surface, sometimes it looks like nothing. But it's nice to watch (most of the time).

Buy it only if you like it!

Click = pause
S = save png
(Live Mode)

metadata.name: Hexagones - Art for Bots #21
metadata.description:
Not for Humans.

Sometimes after rapid drops, bots are set up to watch for blockchain contracts and activity, often getting in on the action before people with wallets and using UI front-ends can. Price your drop too low, and the bots will scoop everything up before anyone has seen anything.

Sometimes we make art for the bots. They wait, watch, and buy and flip before moving on, indifferent to what they see and do. These (coincidentally Twitter icon orientated) hexagons will make the bots hearts go [beep] [boop], before becoming hexagones.

Instructions ::

h - toggle high-res
s - download and save image

metadata.name: Solace #207
metadata.description:
Solace is an algorithm that generates artworks of sand dunes. It draws hundreds of thousands of tiny points according to a probability distribution calculated from the positions of the dunes.

The logic to divide the dunes into light and dark sides is simple, but produces some interesting chaotic behaviour. These are details that weren't hard-coded but emerge organically, such as the patterns on the spines of the dunes or the stripes around their bases.

Please note that the algorithm can take some time to run, especially when the number of dunes is high.

Created by lunarean.
